    "instruction": "How to evaluate this rule:\nDuring the resume matching stage, inspect the structured work experience entries in the work_experience field of the provided resume for any employment record where the company name is OPPO, 小米, or their affiliated companies (关联公司). If such a record exists, check the departure date (离职日期) of that experience and calculate the interval between that departure date and the current date. This rule fires if the interval is less than 6 months. If no such employment record exists, or if the interval is 6 months or greater, this rule does not fire.\n\nWhat to do when this rule fires:\nSet the terminal flag to true and stop further evaluation. Suspend the candidate's matching recommendation process. Generate and append a to-do task notification titled \"竞对互不挖角待确认\" to the notifications array (no schema available), addressed to the recruiter indicated by the recruiter_employee_id field of the relevant Application object. Do not continue the normal matching flow for this candidate.\n\nHow to verify before moving on:\nVerify that the terminal flag is set to true and that further evaluation has been stopped. Verify that the notifications array contains the newly appended \"竞对互不挖角待确认\" to-do task notification addressed to the recruiter. Verify that the candidate's matching recommendation process remains suspended and has not proceeded to the next step.",
