    "description": "What this step accomplishes:\nThis step performs item-by-item matching of a candidate against the hard requirements of job requisitions (招聘岗位), including degree requirements (统招/非统招、本科/硕士等), work years, skill certificates, age range, and other hard requirements. It exists in the action's procedure to calculate, based on the And/Or logic relationships confirmed during the clarification stage, whether the candidate satisfies the hard conditions, and if not satisfied, to mark the candidate as a mismatch. The step uses the input candidate_id, which is the candidate's unique identifier, to read the Candidate fields highest_acquired_degree, birth_date, gender, experience_years, nationality, marital_fertility_status, and gap_reason to perform item-by-item hard requirement comparison. It uses the input resume_id, which is the candidate's resume identifier, to read the Resume fields work_experience, education_experience, skill_tags, language_skills, and certificate to compare against the job's hard requirements. It uses the input job_requisition_ids, which is the list of job requisitions that have passed red-line validation, to read from each job requisition the hard requirement fields degree_requirement, must_have_skills, language_requirements, age_range, gender, salary_range, and work_schedule_type. It uses the input candidate_expectation, which is the unique identifier of the candidate's job expectation record (FK→Candidate_Expectation), to query the Candidate_Expectation object and read the expected_salary_range and outsourcing_acceptance_level fields, which are used respectively for salary expectation upper limit validation and outsourcing willingness validation. The step produces the output hard_match_result, which is a hard requirement matching result where each job requisition contains a pass/fail status and item-by-item comparison details across dimensions (学历/技能/年龄/薪资/语言等) and mismatch reasons if any.\n\nHow to perform this step:\nEvaluate the rules in the following order: 10-21, 10-5, 10-14, 10-35, 10-13, 10-12, 10-11, 10-6, 10-15, 10-22, 10-8, 10-47, 10-7, 10-36, 10-30, 10-54, 10-31, 10-9, 10-10. For each job requisition in the input job_requisition_ids, perform item-by-item matching of the candidate against the job requisition's hard requirements, including degree requirements such as 统招/非统招 and 本科/硕士等, work years, skill certificates, age range, and other hard requirements. To perform this matching, read the Candidate fields highest_acquired_degree, birth_date, gender, experience_years, nationality, marital_fertility_status, and gap_reason using the input candidate_id; read the Resume fields work_experience, education_experience, skill_tags, language_skills, and certificate using the input resume_id; read the Job_Requisition fields degree_requirement, must_have_skills, language_requirements, age_range, gender, salary_range, and work_schedule_type from each job requisition; and query the Candidate_Expectation object using the input candidate_expectation to read expected_salary_range and outsourcing_acceptance_level, which are used respectively for salary expectation upper limit validation and outsourcing willingness validation. Apply the And/Or logic relationships confirmed during the clarification stage to calculate whether the hard conditions are satisfied; if the hard conditions are not satisfied, mark the candidate as a mismatch. If any rule has severity \"blocker\" and fires, stop execution immediately. Accumulate findings from non-blocker rules into the step's intermediate output. No conditions under which this step is skipped or short-circuited are specified in the step description.\n\nWhen this step is complete:\nThis step is complete when all rules have been evaluated for all job requisitions in job_requisition_ids, or when a blocker rule has fired and execution has stopped. The intermediate output structure hard_match_result is now populated, containing for each job requisition a pass/fail status and item-by-item comparison details across dimensions (学历/技能/年龄/薪资/语言等) and mismatch reasons if any. If a blocker fired, stop; otherwise proceed to the next step.",
